HEADWORD: Fellow-commoner
<hw>Fel"low-com"mon*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A student
at Cambridge University, England, who <xex>commons</xex>, or dines, at
the Fellow's table.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

